<h1 id="list-all-teams">Teams</h1>

<h2>List all teams</h2>

<p>
  By default, this endpoint retrieves all the teams.
  <br>
  Teams can be filtered by name.
</p>

<p>
  Things to consider:
</p>

<ul>
  <li>
    Teams are <strong>sorted</strong> by alphabetical order based on their name.
  </li>
  <li>
    There is <strong>no pagination</strong>.
  </li>
</ul>

<h3>Endpoint</h3>

<code>GET /v2/teams</code>

<h3>Parameters</h3>

<p>Use them to filter out the results.</p>

<table class="u-full-width">
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Filter</th>
      <th>Optional</th>
      <th>Description</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td><code>search</code></td>
      <td>true</td>
      <td>
        When provided, it returns only the teams which name contains the given value.
        <br>
        Note that it is <strong>case insensitive</strong>.
      </td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<h3>Request example</h3>

<code>curl "/v2/teams"</code>

<h3>Response example</h3>

<pre><code>{
  "teams": [
    {
      "id": 6,
      "name": "Business Development",
    },
    {
      "id": 11,
      "name":  "Channels"
    },
    {
      "id": 7,
      "name": "Customer Success"
    }
  ]
}</code></pre>
